The effect of the test compounds 19 and 20 on cell surface hydrophobicity was investigated via the microbial or bacterial adherence to hydrocarbons (MATH / BATH) assay [55, 62]. Exponentially growing culture of P. aeruginosa ATCC 27953 incubated with or without test compounds were centrifuged, the pellets were re-suspended and OD600 was measured using UV/Vis spectrophotometer (Jasco V-630, Tokyo, Japan) to give Ao. The re-suspended cells were vigorously mixed with toluene followed by measuring the OD600 of the aqueous phase to give At. The hydrophobicity index was calculated as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
